z einer »Helden-Semiotik« ausgegangen werden kann und welche Schlussfolgerungen sich daraus für synchrone und diachrone Heldenkonzeptionen ziehen lassen.  aThe contributors to the volume develop a semiotic model for understanding a broad spectrum of heroic figures, from giants and medieval heroes to Batman and Doctor Who. Central to this model is the relationship between the heroic figure and its characteristic inventory of symbols.  afunded by Universitätsbund Tübingen e.V.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aHeroesxHistory. 4aAllgemeine Literaturwissenschaft. 4aFilm. 4aFrühe Neuzeit. 4aHeroismus. 4aKulturgeschichte. 4aKunst. 4aLesbarkeit. 4aLiteratur. 4aLiteraturwissenschaft. 4aMittelalter. 4aMittelalterliche Geschichte. 4aModerne. 4aSemiotik. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aLiterary studies.  aMiddle Ages.  acultural history.  aheroism.  amedieval history.  amodernity.  asemiotics.1 aBeek, Lena van, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDäumer, Matthias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFahr, Svenja, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFederow, Anne-Katrin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJansen, Daria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNieser, Florian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNieser, Florian, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aOlbert, Ann-Kathrin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPawlak, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSahm, Heike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTetzlaff, Stefan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.g